\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Tarea 3: El aparato de Frenet
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Jose Antonio Lorencio Abril
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Dada una curva regular en 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{\mathbb{R}^{3}}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{\alpha:I\subset\mathbb{R}\rightarrow\mathbb{R}^{3}}$
\end_inset

, su aparato de Frenet es la familia 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{\left\{ k,\tau,T,N,B\right\} }$
\end_inset

 formada por su curvatura, su torsión y su triedro de Frenet.
 Calcule el aparato de Frenet de la siguiente curva:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\boldsymbol{\alpha\left(s\right)=\left(3s-s^{3},3s^{2},3s+s^{3}\right)}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Debemos tener cuidado al hacer esto, pues las definiciones del libro están
 dadas para curvas p.p.a..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Por la proposición 1.3.5, podemos obtener 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Tenemos, primero, que
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha'=\left(3-3s^{2},6s,3+3s^{2}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha''=\left(-6s,6,6s\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha'''=\left(-6,0,6\right)
\]

\end_inset

 Por lo que
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha\land\alpha'=\left|\begin{array}{ccc}
i & j & k\\
3-3s^{2} & 6s & 3+3s^{2}\\
-6s & 6 & 6s
\end{array}\right|=\left(36s^{2}-18-18s^{2},-18s-18s^{2}-18s+18s^{2},18-18s^{2}+36s^{2}\right)=
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\left(18s^{2}-18,-36s,18s^{2}+18\right)=18\left(s^{2}-1,-2s,s^{2}+1\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
k=\frac{\left|\alpha'\land\alpha''\right|}{\left|\alpha'\right|^{3}}=\frac{\sqrt{18}\sqrt{s^{4}+1-2s^{2}+4s^{2}+s^{4}+1+2s^{2}}}{\left(9+9s^{4}-18s^{2}+36s^{2}+9+9s^{4}+18s^{2}\right)^{\frac{3}{2}}}=\frac{\sqrt{18}\sqrt{2s^{4}+2+6s^{2}}}{\left(18+18s^{4}+36s^{2}\right)^{\frac{3}{2}}}=\frac{\sqrt{18}\sqrt{2}\sqrt{s^{4}+3s^{2}+1}}{\sqrt{18}^{3}\sqrt{1+2s^{2}+s^{4}}^{3}}=
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{18}\sqrt{\frac{1+3s^{2}+s^{4}}{1+2s^{2}+s^{4}}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_body
